+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01N8a5rs3rDb61meKNgmWNfx","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of the entire codebase structure.\n\n## Complete Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Directory Layout\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── index.ts (exports)\n│   │   ├── types.ts (Plugin interface & types)\n│   │   ├── engine.ts (BuildEngine with DAG resolver)\n│   │   └── templates.ts (default & list templates)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       └── .gitkeep (empty - needs 8 plugins)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts (BuildEngine tests)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       ├── rss-feed.test.ts\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n│       └── dev-server.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n└── vitest.config.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Plugin Interface (from `/workspace/src/core/types.ts`)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Build Engine (`/workspace/src/core/engine.ts`)\n\nThe **BuildEngine** class features:\n\n- **Plugin Management**: `registerPlugin()`, `getPlugins()`\n- **Template Management**: `registerTemplate()`, `getTemplates()`\n- **Topological Sorting** (`resolvePluginOrder()`):\n  - Uses depth-first search to detect circular dependencies\n  - Throws on circular dependencies or missing dependencies\n  - Returns plugins in execution order based on their `dependencies` array\n\n- **Build Process** (`async build(files: ContentFile[])`):\n  1. Creates BuildContext with config, files, output Map, assets Map, data Map\n  2. Resolves plugin order via topological sort\n  3. Executes `beforeBuild` hooks in order\n  4. Applies `transformContent` hooks to each file in plugin order\n  5. Renders all files using templates (or outputs raw content)\n  6. Executes `afterBuild` hooks in order\n  7. Returns populated BuildContext\n\n---\n\n### 4. Templates (`/workspace/src/core/templates.ts`)\n\n**Two built-in templates:**\n\n1. **`default` template**: Renders full HTML with `<article>` wrapper\n2. **`list` template**: Renders with `<div class=\"list\">` wrapper\n\nBoth receive data object with: `title`, `slug`, `date`, `tags`, custom metadata, `siteTitle`, `baseUrl`\n\n---\n\n### 5. Core Tests (`/workspace/tests/core.test.ts`)\n\n**Key test coverage:**\n- Plugin registration and retrieval\n- Template registration\n- Default template rendering (checks for DOCTYPE, title, content)\n- List template rendering\n- Raw content output when no template\n- Plugin hook execution (beforeBuild, transformContent, afterBuild)\n- Content transformation through plugin hooks\n- Plugin dependency resolution (topological sort)\n- Circular dependency detection\n- Missing dependency detection\n- Multiple plugins transforming content in order\n- Shared data store in build context\n- Metadata persistence through build\n- Empty file list handling\n\n---\n\n### 6. The 8 Required Plugins (from test files)\n\n#### **Plugin 1: markdown-ext** (`tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts`)\n- **Hook**: `transformContent`\n- **Purpose**: Converts markdown to HTML with extensions\n- **Features**:\n  - Convert basic markdown (headers, bold, etc.) to HTML\n  - Parse footnotes with `[^1]` syntax\n  - Render footnote section at bottom with `<section class=\"footnotes\">`\n  - Convert `:::note`, `:::warning`, `:::tip` blocks to `<div class=\"admonition admonition-TYPE\">`\n  - Preserve existing HTML in content\n  - Handle empty content\n- **Expected exports**: `createMarkdownExtPlugin()` function\n\n#### **Plugin 2: asset-pipeline** (`tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts`)\n- **Hook**: `transformContent`\n- **Purpose**: Rewrite asset URLs and track asset manifest\n- **Features**:\n  - Rewrite relative image URLs (`./image.png`) to `/assets/image.png`\n  - Rewrite relative link URLs (`<a href=\"./doc.pdf\">`) to `/assets/doc.pdf`\n  - Leave absolute URLs unchanged (https://...)\n  - Track discovered assets in `ctx.data.set('asset-manifest', { assets: string[] })`\n  - Skip already-rewritten `/assets/` URLs\n  - Handle multiple assets per file\n  - Accumulate assets across all files\n- **Expected exports**: `createAssetPipelinePlugin()` function\n\n#### **Plugin 3: taxonomy** (`tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts`)\n- **Hooks**: `beforeBuild`, `afterBuild`\n- **Purpose**: Build tag index and generate tag pages\n- **Features**:\n  - In `beforeBuild`: Build tag index from file tags, store in `ctx.data.set('taxonomy-tags', Map<string, ContentFile[]>)`\n  - Normalize tags to lowercase\n  - In `afterBuild`: Generate tag listing pages at `tags/TAG.html`\n  - Tag pages list