ose**: Enhance code block highlighting\n- **Features**:\n  - Add `highlighted` class to code blocks with `language-*` class\n  - Add `data-language=\"LANG\"` attribute to `<pre>` tags\n  - Handle multiple code blocks in one file\n  - Skip code blocks without language specified\n  - Do NOT modify inline `<code>` tags (only `<pre><code>`)\n  - Preserve code block content\n  - Handle empty code blocks\n- **Expected exports**: `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()` function\n\n#### **Plugin 8: dev-server** (`tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts`)\n- **Hook**: `afterBuild`\n- **Purpose**: Generate dev server configuration\n- **Features**:\n  - Store `dev-server-config` in `ctx.data`\n  - Config structure: `{ port: number, routes: Array<{path, handler}>, assetPaths: string[], searchIndexPath: string }`\n  - Default port: 3000\n  - Include asset routes from `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')`\n  - Include search index path from `ctx.output`\n  - Include content routes for all output pages\n  - Handle missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\n- **Expected exports**: `createDevServerPlugin()` function\n\n---\n\n### 7. Build/Test/Lint Configuration\n\n**package.json** (`/workspace/package.json`):\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-ssg-toolkit\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"main\": \"dist/core/index.js\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@types/express\": \"^5.0.6\",\n    \"@types/marked\": \"^5.0.2\",\n    \"express\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"marked\": \"^17.0.2\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.57.1\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.9\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**vitest.config.ts** (`/workspace/vitest.config.ts`):\n```typescript\n- globals: true (use describe/it/expect without imports)\n- testTimeout: 10000ms\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. TypeScript Configuration (`/workspace/tsconfig.json`)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Dependency System**: Plugins declare dependencies by name in the `dependencies` array. The engine uses topological sort to ensure correct execution order.\n\n2. **Data Sharing**: `BuildContext.data` is a Map that plugins use to pass data to each other:\n   - `asset-pipeline` → sets `asset-manifest`\n   - `taxonomy` → sets `taxonomy-tags`\n   - `dev-server` → reads from both and sets `dev-server-config`\n\n3. **Plugin Hook Pattern**:\n   - `beforeBuild`: Called once, for setup (e.g., taxonomy building)\n   - `transformContent`: Called for each file (e.g., markdown conversion, URL rewriting)\n   - `afterBuild`: Called once, for finalization (e.g., sitemap/feed generation)\n\n4. **Available Libraries**:\n   - **marked**: For markdown parsing (^17.0.2)\n   - **express**: Type definitions available (^5.0.6)\n   - Both are installed and ready to use\n\n5. **Expected Plugin File Locations**: Each plugin should be in `/workspace/src/plugins/` with name pattern like `markdown-ext.ts`, `asset-pipeline.ts`, etc.\n\n6. **Dependency Order for Plugins**:\n   - `markdown-ext`: No dependencies (converts content)\n   - `asset-pipeline`: After markdown-ext (rewrites URLs)\n   - `syntax-highlight`: After markdown-ext (enhances code blocks)\n   - `taxonomy`: No dependencies (requires files before transforms)\n   - `sitemap`: Depends on `taxonomy` (needs tag pages)\n   - `rss-feed`: Depends on `taxonomy` (needs category data)\n   - `search-index`: No dependencies (reads from ctx.files)\n   - `dev-server`: After all others (reads asset manifest, search index, routes)\n\n---\n\nYou now have **complete details of all 8 plugins** with comprehensive test specifications to implement them!"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5d96bd (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 33987\ntool_uses: 19\nduration_ms: 39778</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"564c26e2-ad17-491e-9d10-f6e4f67df875","uuid":"14b97b3e-2ce1-4fcf-92f5-6702d2ae3aa9","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the full codebase structure. I need to understand:\n1. The directory layout (all files)\n2. The Plugin interface from src/core/types.ts\n3. The build engine in src/core/\n4. All test files in tests/plugins/ (read every one of them completely)\n5. The existing tests in tests/core.test.ts\n6. package.json for build/test/lint config\n7. tsconfig.json\n\nRead ALL files completely - I need every detail to implement 8 plugins.","agentId":"a5d96bd","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of the entire codebase structure.\n\n## Complete Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Directory Layout\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── index.ts (exports)\n│   │   ├── types.ts (Plugin interface & types)\n│   │   ├── engine.ts (BuildEngine with DAG resolver)\n│   │   └── templates.ts (default & list templates)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       └── .gitkeep (empty - needs 8 plugins)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts (BuildEngine tests)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       ├── rss-feed.test.ts\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n│       └── dev-server.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n└── vitest.config.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Plugin Interface (from `/workspace/src/core/types.ts`)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Build Engine (`/workspace/src/core/engine.ts`)\n\nThe **BuildEngine** class features:\n\n- **Plugin Management**: `registerPlugin()`, `getPlugins()`\n- **Template Management**: `registerTemplate()`, `getTemplates()`\n- **Topological Sorting** (`resolvePluginOrder()`):\n  - Uses depth-first search to detect circular dependencies\n  - Throws on circular dependencies or missing dependencies\n  - Returns plugins in execution order based on their `dependencies` array\n\n- **Build Process** (`async build(files: ContentFile[])`):\n  1. Creates BuildContext with config, files, output Map, assets Map, data Map\n  2. Resolves plugin order via topological sort\n  3. Executes `beforeBuild` hooks in order\n  4. Applies `transformContent` hooks to each file in plugin order\n  5. Renders all files using templates (or outputs raw content)\n  6. Executes `afterBuild` hooks in order\n  7. Returns populated BuildContext\n\n---\n\n### 4. Templates (`/workspace/src/core/templates.ts`)\n\n**Two built-in templates:**\n\n1. **`default` template**: Renders full HTML with `<article>` wrapper\n2. **`list` template**: Renders with `<div class=\"list\">` wrapper\n\nBoth receive data object with: `title`, `slug`, `date`, `tags`, custom metadata, `siteTitle`, `baseUrl`\n\n---\n\n### 5. Core Tests (`/workspace/tests/core.test.ts`)\n\n**Key test coverage:**\n- Plugin registration and retrieval\n- Template registration\n- Default template rendering (checks for DOCTYPE, title, content)\n- List template rendering\n- Raw content output when no template\n- Plugin hook execution (beforeBuild, transformContent, afterBuild)\n- Content transformation through plugin hooks\n- Plugin dependency resolution (topological sort)\n- Circular dependency detection\n- Missing dependency detection\n- Multiple plugins transforming content in order\n- Shared data store in build context\n- Metadata persistence through build\n- Empty file list handling\n\n---\n\n### 6. The 8 Required Plugins (from test files)\n\n#### **Plugin 1: markdown-ext** (`tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts`)\n- **Hook**: `transformContent`\n- **Purpose**: Converts markdown to HTML with extensions\n- **Features**:\n  - Convert basic markdown (headers, bold, etc.) to HTML\n  - Parse footnotes with `[^1]` syntax\n  - Render footnote section at bottom with `<section class=\"footnotes\">`\n  - Convert `:::note`, `:::warning`, `:::tip` blocks to `<div class=\"admonition admonition-TYPE\">`\n  - Preserve existing HTML in content\n  - Handle empty content\n- **Expected exports**: `createMarkdownExtPlugin()` function\n\n#### **Plugin 2: asset-pipeline** (`tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts`)\n- **Hook**: `transformContent`\n- **Purpose**: Rewrite asset URLs and track asset manifest\n- **Features**:\n  - Rewrite relative image URLs (`./image.png`) to `/assets/image.png`\n  - Rewrite relative link URLs (`<a href=\"./doc.pdf\">`) to `/assets/doc.pdf`\n  - Leave absolute URLs unchanged (https://...)\n  - Track discovered assets in `ctx.data.set('asset-manifest', { assets: string[] })`\n  - Skip already-rewritten `/assets/` URLs\n  - Handle multiple assets per file\n  - Accumulate assets across all files\n- **Expected exports**: `createAssetPipelinePlugin()` function\n\n#### **Plugin 3: taxonomy** (`tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts`)\n- **Hooks**: `beforeBuild`, `afterBuild`\n- **Purpose**: Build tag index and generate tag pages\n- **Features**:\n  - In `beforeBuild`: Build tag index from file tags, store in `ctx.data.set('taxonomy-tags', Map<string, ContentFile[]>)`\n  - Normalize tags to lowercase\n  - In `afterBuild`: Generate tag listing pages at `tags/TAG.html`\n  - Tag pages list all files with that tag\n  - Handle files with no tags\n  - Handle multiple tags per file\n  - Handle empty file list\n- **Expected exports**: `createTaxonomyPlugin()` function\n\n#### **Plugin 4: sitemap** (`tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts`)\n- **Hook**: `afterBuild`\n- **Purpose**: Generate XML sitemap\n- **Features**:\n  - Generate `sitemap.xml` in `ctx.output`\n  - Include all content page URLs\n  - Include taxonomy tag page URLs (from `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')`)\n  - Include feed.xml URL\n  - Use baseUrl from config\n  - Valid XML structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"...` + `<urlset>...</urlset>` with `<url><loc>` entries\n  - Handle missing tag pages gracefully\n- **Expected exports**: `createSitemapPlugin()` function\n\n#### **Plugin 5: rss-feed** (`tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts`)\n- **Hook**: `afterBuild`\n- **Purpose**: Generate RSS 2.0 feed\n- **Features**:\n  - Generate `feed.xml` in `ctx.output`\n  - Valid RSS 2.0 XML structure with `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>`\n  - Include file HTML content in CDATA sections: `<![CDATA[...HTML...]]>`\n  - Include category tags from `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')`\n  - Channel 